model_explanation: the use of "only" in S1 means that Sue was the exclusive recipient of apples. S2 contradicts this by saying that Rob also received apples.
the sentence about Mary in S2 is independent and doesn’t affect the statement in S1 about Bill being the only recipient of apples.
the word "only" indicates that Mary was the sole recipient of oranges. S2 contradicts S1 by stating that Ellen was also a recipient of oranges.
the statement about Tom in S2 is independent of S1. S1 is about Ellen being the only recipient of apples, while S2 doesn’t affect or contradict that claim.
S1 states that Rob was the only person who received bananas. S2 says something about oranges, which is independent of the claim about bananas.
S1 says Bill received only bananas, and S2 (saying Bill didn’t get grapes) aligns with that. There’s no contradiction, and S2 is entailed by S1.
if Ellen only received oranges (S1), then she didn’t receive grapes. S2 is entailed by S1.
S1 talks about Mary being the only recipient of bananas. S2 involves Ellen and is independent of whether Mary got bananas or not.
if Bill was the only recipient of bananas, then it follows that Tom didn’t get bananas. S2 is entailed by S1.
if Sue only received oranges, it means she received no other fruit. Therefore, S2 (saying she didn’t get grapes) is entailed by S1.
